Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay medium light brown; mainly white inclusions; some mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Close to Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 49, but unlikely to be identical. Clay rather Cyrenaic. Extent of stamp unclear; perhaps chipped during trimming by Petrie?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1673)
